quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  29,24,"The only response of Abraham's people was, \"Kill him or burn him!\" But God saved him from the fire. Surely in this there are signs for people who believe"
  29,25,"Abraham said, \"You have taken up the worship of idols, instead of God, to promote friendship between yourselves in the present life. But on the Day of Judgement, you will disown and curse one another. Your abode will be the Fire and you will have no helpers"
  29,26,"Lot was the one who believed in him and said, \"I shall migrate to another land for the sake of my Lord. He is the Mighty One, the Wise One"
  29,27,We gave him Isaac and Jacob and granted prophethood and the Book to his descendants. We gave him his reward in this life and in the Hereafter he shall dwell among the righteous
  29,28,"We sent Lot to his people and he said to them, \"Indeed you commit obscenity such as no people before you have ever committed"
  29,29,"You approach men and waylay them on the road and commit depravities within your gatherings.\" But his people's only reply was, \"Bring down God's punishment upon us, if what you say be true"
  29,30,"Lot prayed, \"Lord, help me against this wicked people"